\cf2 \cb3 The Top 25 Investing Quotes of All Time\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 CLOSE\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/bloomberg_terminal.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 Bloomberg terminal}}\'a0is one of the industry's most widely used sources for real-time financial information. This guide is aimed at new Bloomberg users and will provide an overview of how to use a Bloomberg terminal. If you want to go into more detail on Bloomberg's capabilities, please be on the lookout for the Advanced Guide to Bloomberg.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Here we'll examine how to sign up for, install, and access Bloomberg. We'll then cover basic navigation on the Bloomberg system. Navigating Bloomberg is somewhat unique in that the system uses a special keyboard with some keys that are different from those found on a "normal" keyboard.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 We'll discuss some of the market and news monitor functions available on Bloomberg after gaining a working knowledge of these basics.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 KEY TAKEAWAYS\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The Bloomberg Terminal has been an indispensable data and information system for financial professionals since 1981.\cf8 \super 1\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Subscribers can download and run the Bloomberg software on a PC or Mac.\cb1 \
\ls1\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Today's terminal offers a wealth of news and headlines, real-time quotes in numerous markets, tools for fundamental and technical analysis, and economic research.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \cb3 Get personalized, AI-powered answers built on 27+ years of trusted expertise.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \cb10 ASK\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Installation and Access\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You can begin using Bloomberg in two ways. The first is to subscribe to the Bloomberg service. You can do so by contacting them. The general contact number for the Americas is (212) 318-2000, but other locations have different numbers.\cf8 \super 2\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The representative you speak with can take down details of what you're looking for and have someone from the sales team contact you. Pricing and terms of the contract are unique to each user and will be discussed when the sales team contacts you.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa127\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 IMPORTANT\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg is an expensive system, and having your own terminal may not be practical for all users.\cf8 \super 3\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The software can be installed on most PCs or Macs, but the company will give you a special keyboard for navigating the system.\cf8 \super 4\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The second method of accessing Bloomberg is to find a public facility with a Bloomberg terminal. Many larger libraries and universities have one, so that's a good place to start looking.\cf8 \super 5\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The downside of this approach is that you won't be able to customize the system, and you'll have to share it with other users. These drawbacks may be outweighed by the cost savings of subscribing to the system as an individual for many users, however.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The next trick is to figure out how to navigate the system. A good starting point would be to schedule a visit from a Bloomberg customer service representative or call customer service for help. Bloomberg is usually quite good at providing technical support and assistance.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 {{\NeXTGraphic Screenshot2024-08-12at1.55.53PM-d98280b5a2ca4ab1bd989dd247ff2947.png.webp \width15000 \height10800 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 The Bloomberg Terminal Log-In Page.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The screenshot above shows the Bloomberg log-in page. Each user has a username and password that will allow them to access the system, although you might have to share this with other users at public facilities. You're ready to begin using the Bloomberg system after you've logged in.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Basic Navigation\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The Bloomberg terminal is a Windows-based application, making it compatible with the popular Excel program, a very important aspect of the system for those in the finance industry. Bloomberg also offers users access to the application online and through mobile devices via its Bloomberg Anywhere service.\cf8 \super 6\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Accessing real-time market information from almost anywhere in the world is an incredibly convenient and important advantage of a Bloomberg subscription for\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/portfoliomanager.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 portfolio managers}}\'a0and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/broker.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 brokers}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The first thing most people notice when they sit down in front of a Bloomberg terminal is the keyboard. It's similar to a standard desktop keyboard, but Bloomberg terminals substitute the function keys on a standard keyboard (i.e., F4) with market sector keys.\cf8 \super 7\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg keyboards also incorporate color coding to make them more intuitive. The function keys along the top of the keyboard are mostly color-coded yellow, and they allow a user to navigate by asset class: government bonds, corporate bonds, municipals, commodities, equities, and currencies.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 If a user is interested in examining a stock, they'll generally access it through the key. If they want to look at trading the U.S. dollar versus the euro, most functions would be accessed with the key.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 There are also special function keys for\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/p/preferredstock.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 preferred stocks}}\'a0and funds. The Bloomberg keyboard has a special key for communicating with other users via email or instant message, as well as a key that can be used when you require assistance.\cf8 \super 8\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 {{\NeXTGraphic 2640x320keyboard-e10d95a82bb045bf83f398e48a45f469.png.webp \width15000 \height6220 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Image courtesy of Wikipedia.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg Tickers\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg uses abbreviations and tickers for most of its functions. Someone looking for a quote on Microsoft stock would type in the symbol for Microsoft (MSFT), followed by the key, and then hit enter.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 This would bring up a menu of options relating to Microsoft stock. Very few users know more than a small fraction of the almost limitless number of available Bloomberg options, so these menus present an excellent way to see what sort of analytics are available for a given security or market.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You might begin to memorize some of the shortcuts after you're familiar with Bloomberg, saving a step for familiar functions rather than going through the menu.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 If you want to see the basic description page for Microsoft's stock, you could type this in and then hit enter instead of accessing it through the menu. The "des" is the abbreviation for description pages on Bloomberg, and this common function will provide a good general overview of most securities.\cf8 \super 9\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 There are an almost unlimited number of functions in Bloomberg, so the best way to begin navigating the system is probably to use menus and then select your favorite functions from there. You can begin to memorize the shortcuts for your most commonly used functions over time while continuing to use the menus for less frequent choices.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Help\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You'll notice that there's a green key on the Bloomberg keyboard. This can be your best friend, especially when you're new to the system. You can get information about the screen that you're currently viewing by hitting the help key once.\cf8 \super 10\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Hitting it twice will send an instant message to the Bloomberg help desk. You can then ask your question via live chat with a Bloomberg specialist who can guide you on using the terminal as well as whatever particular function you're trying to access.\cf8 \super 11\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Messaging\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 One of the nice features of Bloomberg is that it has a fairly robust messaging system. This system allows users to stay in contact with other users and is one of the reasons that Bloomberg is so ubiquitous in the financial industry.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You can look up other users of the system to send them a message, and you can set them up on speed dial as well if you contact someone regularly.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You have two choices when messaging. The first is to send a traditional message, which is basically like an email. The second is to open up an instant message window with the other user, which is similar to traditional instant messaging. Both methods work great, so which one you choose is largely a matter of personal preference.\cf8 \super 12\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 News and Market Monitors\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 A common use of the Bloomberg terminal in addition to analyzing individual securities is to monitor news updates and financial market movements. Here, too, there's an endless array of possibilities. Which one users prefer is often a matter of personal choice.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 There are a couple of common screens that can serve as a starting point for new users. When in doubt, the menu functions can also help here. The general menu that you see for most asset classes, including equities,\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/currency.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 currencies}}, and commodities, will usually contain listings for market monitors that provide a good starting place for analysis.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 News\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The best place to begin looking for news on Bloomberg is by typing in its name and then hitting "enter" to search. These functions bring up a page of the top news stories of the day, which are updated on an ongoing basis. Selecting any of these headlines will bring up the full story. There are additional sub-menus within the function that will allow you to view news stories that are filtered by\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/a/assetclasses.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 asset class}}, geographic region, or topic.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You can choose to see the top worldwide stories, the top U.S. stories, or the top stories for stocks, bonds, or almost any other category you choose.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You can also choose to set the default for top news to whichever category you prefer if you're using your own personal Bloomberg. The news category that's most important to you is what you'll see when you type in. The screenshot below shows an example of the screen for the top worldwide news headlines.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 4640x320-69194bad130c4a009296dc0a436eb558.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 News by Geography.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 News can also be customized in a wide variety of other ways. If you're primarily interested in the stock market, you can access top news for stocks.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The stock news screen is further broken down into sections: first for worldwide headlines, then by continent, with North America, followed by Europe, and, finally, Asia. Users seeking even greater detail can click on the regions in white to access stock news headlines specific to a region or country, such as the United States, Canada, or Eastern Europe.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Market Monitor\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 There are several market monitor pages that cover a variety of asset classes, as well as some that cover a single asset class or market sector. The monitor below is accessed by typing the request into your Bloomberg. The PX1 screen is a little bit more focused on the U.S.\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/t/treasurybond.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 Treasury bond}}\'a0market while also giving updates on the Dow, Nasdaq, and S&P, as well as the gold and oil markets.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 5MarketMonitor-ade841f8bc6e44d7b4c894217c4cc094.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Market Monitor.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The screenshot below is another example of a market monitor that's primarily focused on the bond market.\cf8 \super 13\cf2 \nosupersub \'a0This is another bond market screen, but you'll notice that it covers a broader array of securities than the PX1 function. The BTMM screen shows markets for a wide variety of\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/m/moneymarket.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 money market}}\'a0instruments, as well as mortgage-backed bonds and currencies, in addition to U.S. Treasuries. The BTMM screen also includes quotes on the Dow, Nasdaq, and S&P, as well as oil.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Finally, the screen contains a listing of the day's major economic releases, making it easy to keep track of this as well. There are a multitude of additional market monitor screens in addition to PX1 and BTMM that primarily focus on movements in the bond markets. As you can imagine, no one screen is "best," and which one users prefer is ultimately a matter of personal choice.\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 6marketmonitor2-ad8a371c3aa84d45894f9b798da94285.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Another Market Monitor.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 There's also a wide variety of monitors that focus on equity markets. You can pull up the monitor below by typing the request on your keyboard.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 This monitor displays equity\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/i/index.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 index}}\'a0movements from around the globe. You can get more details on additional markets in a given region by drilling down into the menu. By clicking on the "Asia/Pacific" heading, you can access updates on the markets in that region that were unable to fit on the front page due to space constraints.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Any of the headers in a white font with numbers in front of them indicate an additional sub-menu that can be accessed on most of these monitor pages, as well as many other screens. On the screen below, there are "1) Americas", "2) EMEA," and "3) Asia/Pacific," which can all be accessed by either clicking on them or by typing in the appropriate number and hitting enter. There are also choices at the top marked by "95) Settings" and "96) News" that represent sub-menus as well.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 7marketmonitor3-35b05cb6507c490b885aa1b0169d9146.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Market Monitor.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Economics\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The Bloomberg terminal can also be used to monitor\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/e/economics.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 economic}}\'a0forecasts and releases. This page gives a listing of all upcoming economic data releases, as well as consensus forecasts of what economists at major banks and brokerages are predicting those numbers will be. The ECO screen also shows the actual number upon release, as well as any revisions to the previous month's report. There's an ECO page for most major economies for those interested in overseas markets.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You can access economic forecasts and data from Europe, China, and elsewhere by using the dropdown menus for "Region" and "Country." The screenshot below displays a basic ECO screen with data for the United States.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 8Economics-acd2e653ee69479fb4383cad28e0da49.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Economics.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Analyzing Securities and Currencies\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg can also be used to analyze individual securities. The analytics available in Bloomberg are quite robust, and they cover several major asset classes, including equities,\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/f/fixedincome.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 fixed income}}, currencies, commodities, mutual funds, and ETFs.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 This guide will attempt to cover some of the available basic functions. Contact a Bloomberg representative for training to learn more, read Investopedia's Advanced Bloomberg Guide, or explore additional functions in a hands-on manner.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You can find the ticker by hitting the key for the asset class you're looking at if you're uncertain what the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/s/stocksymbol.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 ticker symbol}}\'a0is for a security you want to look at. You could type in Microsoft and hit enter, and the ticker would appear if you wanted to analyze Microsoft stock but didn't know the ticker.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Using this function will pull up a list of all the tickers for that company. All of them will appear if a stock is listed on multiple exchanges, so it's important to make sure you select the correct security from the list when using this function. Most users would be looking for the ticker for Microsoft stock listed on the Nasdaq stock exchange in this example.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The basic screen for beginning security analysis is the description page, Bloomberg abbreviation, after you have the correct ticker. The screenshot below shows page one of the Bloomberg description for Microsoft stock. Similar screens are also available for many types of bonds and other asset classes.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 As you can see, the description page provides a brief overview of what the company does, as well as basic information such as a price quote, 52-week high and low,\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/m/marketcapitalization.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 market capitalization}},\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/e/eps.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 earnings per share}}, P/E Ratio, and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/d/dividendyield.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 dividend yield}}. The page below is only the first page of 10 pages of security description information.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You can access additional information by scrolling forward, including contact details for the company and a breakdown of the company's revenue and earnings by geographic region and market segment. You can also find detailed financial data such as an income statement, cash flow statement, and balance sheet.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The financial data can sometimes be a bit dated, so you might want to double-check the date listed next to the financial statements if seeing the most recent data is important to you.\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 9Analysis1-0f218ab54ead4b54b71dde6068730dde.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Analysis.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg can also be used to analyze a security's price history and trading patterns. Users can access a price history for whatever security they're looking at by typing this request into the system.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg offers an advanced suite of charting capabilities for users interested in more advanced technical analysis.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 A complete description of available charts is beyond the scope of this article, but some of the tools available include\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/r/rsi.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 relative strength indicators}}\'a0(RSI),\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/bollingerbands.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 Bollinger Bands\'ae}}, intraday price and volume charts, candlestick charts, and comparison charts displaying multiple securities. An example of a simple price and volume chart for Microsoft stock is displayed below.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 10Analysis2-a5aec147b8174a07b5d63bcfdea28cf4.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Analysis.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg also provides easy access to company updates. It offers company-specific news in addition to the top news stories discussed.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 You can type into Bloomberg, and a scrolling list of the most recent news stories concerning that security will come up after you've pulled up a security, such as Microsoft stock. You can then click on any of those headlines to read the full story.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Additional security-specific information that can be found on Bloomberg includes earnings estimates (Bloomberg\'a0ticker\'a0EE), analyst recommendations (Bloomberg ticker ANR), and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/creditrating.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 credit ratings}}\'a0(Bloomberg ticker CRPR).\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Equities\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg allows users to search by name, exchange, country, and other such topics when they're searching for publicly traded equity shares.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The equity menu also allows users to view historical pricing on a stock, read a description of the business, view any outstanding corporate debt the company may have, and view analyst reports and estimates for the stock, along with dozens of other features. This menu also allows users to search for indices such as the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/s/sp500.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 S&P 500}}\'a0or Russell 2000.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 11Equities-798414c14c7d48668b00dc7b50cf458a.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Equities.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg allows clients to compare and contrast equities side by side, offering a comparative analysis of any two. Comparison fields include\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/f/fundamentalanalysis.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 fundamental analysis}}, historical ratios, and technical charting. Bloomberg also includes screeners, allowing clients to screen for stocks using a multitude of\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/m/metrics.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 metrics}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Users can also filter results and create custom equity sets after running a screen, which allows for a quick reference of real-time results for a portfolio of equities. This can be very handy for\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/t/trader.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 traders}}, brokers, and other such financial professionals.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Fixed Income\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Much like with equities, Bloomberg allows users to search for real-time data on\'a0fixed-income\'a0securities. This includes corporate debt,\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/m/municipalbond.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 municipal bonds}},\'a0and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/g/government-bond.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 government bonds}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Similar to the historical price screen for equities, we can view historical day-over-day changes in security values, along with implied yield-to-maturities, for any given day. Additionally, credit ratings and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/costofcapital.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 cost of capital}}\'a0information are available for fixed-income securities.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Derivatives\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 One of Bloomberg's best features is its derivatives capabilities. Not only can clients find real-time values for securities, such as exchange-traded options and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/f/futurescontract.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 futures contracts}}, but Bloomberg also allows users to value hard-to-price\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/d/derivative.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 derivatives}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 A user can decide to value an OTC option on the S&P 500 using the continuous\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/blackscholes.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 Black-Scholes}}\'a0model, using\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/h/historicalvolatility.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 historical volatility}}. Users can view the values of the Greeks associated with the option in question when priced to verify that their price estimate is in line with those expectations.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb4 {{\NeXTGraphic 12Derivatives-bb64eced856d4fba8c815326e18cca85.jpg.webp \width14640 \height9860 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}洞\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf5 \cb3 Derivatives.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 SWAPS\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 SWAPS are a type of derivative used by large banks and institutional investors. The Bloomberg Terminal has a SWAP manager tool that's a highly customizable swap pricing utility. It allows users to input the parameters of a swap agreement and come up with an estimate for the value of that swap at any given date in time.\cf8 \super 14\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Clients can also view underlying\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/s/swapcurve.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 swap curves}}\'a0to determine that the underlying inputs match\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/e/expected-value.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 expected values}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Foreign Exchange\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg is the ideal tool for FX participants because the FX market is a 24-hour marketplace. Users can view real-time rates for dozens of currencies along with basis curves for most pairs, and rate information for a given currency.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Its FX capabilities are also a very powerful tool for those trading in the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/forex/f/foreign-exchange-markets.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 foreign exchange market}}, with Bloomberg's ability to capture real-time news and economic updates.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Tips and Tricks\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg has such a robust suite of analytics and market capabilities that getting the system to do what you want it to do can be a challenge, at least until you become familiar with it. Fortunately, some tricks can speed up your learning curve.\'a0\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Make use of the function:\'a0Bloomberg provides excellent customer support. Make use of it by hitting the key when you need assistance. Hitting once describes the function you're using. Hitting it twice will connect you to customer support via instant message.\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Schedule a visit from a Bloomberg representative:\'a0Take advantage of a visit from a Bloomberg representative who can walk you through the system and show you how to use some of the functions that might be helpful for what you intend to do, particularly if you have your own system.\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Get Bloomberg "cheat sheets":\'a0Bloomberg puts out "cheat sheets" that list common functions and their Bloomberg tickers. These sheets are broken down by asset class, so get a sheet with the most common equity functions if you intend to analyze equities. Get a fixed income guide if you like fixed income. These "cheat sheets" should give you a good starting point for navigating common Bloomberg functions.\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Visit Bloomberg University:\'a0By typing into the system, you will be taken to a screen that offers a wide variety of training videos, informational papers, and live seminars. The seminars are broken down by region, so you might be interested in attending one in your area. There's a fee for some of the seminars, but the majority are offered free to Bloomberg users.\cb1 \
\ls2\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Incorporate Excel into Bloomberg:\'a0Bloomberg connects rather seamlessly with Excel, so you can use spreadsheets to analyze data downloaded from Bloomberg. Even better, you can build a spreadsheet that automatically updates your data each time you open it, saving you the trouble of doing so by hand.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Best of all, Bloomberg offers sample spreadsheets for common types of analysis, such as tracking stock price movements or analyzing company\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/balancesheet.asp"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 balance sheets}}. This saves you the trouble of building your own spreadsheet. You can further customize these generic spreadsheets that Bloomberg offers to fit your specific needs.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Type to access the Excel main menu on Bloomberg if you're interested in incorporating Excel spreadsheets.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 How Much Does the Bloomberg Terminal Cost?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Bloomberg terminals cost approximately $25,000 a year as of 2024.\cf8 \super 15\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Can You Place Trades From the Bloomberg Terminal?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Yes. You can place orders in several markets using sophisticated order routing and complex order tools.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 How Many Bloomberg Terminal Users Are There?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 According to the company, there's a network of more than 350,000 Bloomberg Terminal users.\cf8 \super 16\cf2 \cb1 \nosupersub \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The Bottom Line\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 This basic guide to Bloomberg has provided an introduction to one of the most practical tools participants in the financial markets can use. Unfortunately, Bloomberg can be expensive, so having a home system may not be practical for many readers.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 On the positive side, it's often possible to access a Bloomberg terminal through a public site such as a library or university. There are so many functions available in Bloomberg that this guide has been able to provide no more than a simple introduction to the system, along with an overview of some common tools that users might find useful. You'll undoubtedly find a great many more tools that fit your particular investment and trading style after you begin using Bloomberg.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Readers interested in a more in-depth examination of Bloomberg may want to keep an eye out for the Advanced Guide to Bloomberg on the Investopedia website. The Advanced Guide will provide more detailed instructions on how Bloomberg can be used to analyze, monitor, and trade some of the major asset classes, including stocks, bonds, currencies, and\'a0commodities.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa420\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Several other tutorials are also available to those interested in learning more, including those offered directly from Bloomberg. Many colleges and universities offer Bloomberg courses to help students gain early exposure to the most widely used tool for real-time financial data in the world of finance. It's just a matter of sitting down with the system and familiarizing yourself with it after you're equipped with some training.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

