\fs40 \cf11 \cb12 The US stock market has not only survived one of the most hectic starts to a trading year on record \'97 it's thriving.\cb1 \
\cb12 After falling 19% in a matter of weeks earlier this year, the S&P 500 ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/%5EGSPC"}}{\fldrslt \cf13 ^GSPC}}) is back at record highs, but a sense of unease about the status of this rally persists.\cb1 \
\cb12 There's the perpetual debate about stock valuations, which are historically elevated, as the stability of the artificial intelligence growth story remains in question for some investors.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf11 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa640\partightenfactor0

\fs40 \cf11 \cb12 The potential fallout from\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/live/trump-tariffs-live-updates-us-eu-deal-details-emerge-as-china-talks-begin-trump-seeks-15-20-world-tariff-200619425.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf13 President Trump's tariff}}\'a0and immigration policies \'97 and their impact on US economic growth \'97 has emerged as the top concern among economists who are still questioning the resilience of the US economy.\cb1 \
\cb12 But the fifth volume of the Yahoo Finance Chartbook also presents a calming explanation for why stocks have inflected higher in a\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/the-v-shaped-recovery-in-stocks-is-a-v-shaped-recovery-in-earnings-chart-of-the-week-100013733.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf13 V-shaped pattern}}\'a0after April brought one of the worst three-day stretches since World War II.\cb1 \
\cb12 Corporate profit expectations are picking up, particularly in areas that have been bid up the most in the market. By some measures, the US consumer remains in solid shape. And even after a\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/a-chaotic-6-months-for-stocks-shows-investors-are-still-leaning-bullish-headed-into-the-second-half-of-2025-191024372.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf13 roaring rally}}, several strategists argue investor sentiment is far from peaking.\cb1 \
\cb12 Trump has also dialed up the pressure on Fed Chair Jerome Powell to cut interest rates, but this edition of the Chartbook shows the central bank taking less of a starring role in this market moment.\cb1 \
\cb12 When and how the central bank adjusts its policy seems a less pressing question than what has prompted stocks to climb this year's wall of worry and what forces could prompt investors to keep climbing.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa640\partightenfactor0
